.TH "extcon_register_notifier" 9 "extcon_register_notifier" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
extcon_register_notifier \- Register a notifier block to get notified by any state changes from the extcon.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" extcon_register_notifier
.BI "(struct extcon_dev *edev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int id "  ","
.BI "struct notifier_block *nb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "edev" 12
the extcon device
.IP "id" 12
the unique id indicating an external connector
.IP "nb" 12
a notifier block to be registered
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that the second parameter given to the callback of nb (val) is
the current state of an external connector and the third pameter
is the pointer of extcon device.

Returns 0 if success or error number if fail.
